 This book offers a deep ethnography of three Delhi bazaars, and a cast of tinkers, traders, magicians, street performers, and hackers who work there. It is an exploration, and recognition, of the role of bazaars and tinkers in the modern global economy, driving globalization from below. In Delhi, and across the world, these street markets work to create a new information society, as the global popular classes aspire to elite consumer goods they cannot afford except in counterfeit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBazaars (Markets)zIndiazDelhi. 0aGlobalizationxEconomic aspectszIndiazDelhi. 0aStreet vendorszIndiazDelhi. 0aTinkerszIndiazDelhi. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Technology Studies.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aBazaar.  aCapitalism.  aCommons.  aDelhi.  aDigital.  aE-Commerce Platform.  aEthics.  aEveryday.  aInnovation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079132740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363601940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503636019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503636019/original  a978-3-11-079132-7  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles